Returned Portraits project by Roberto Pazzi

Piece #11 of 15

This is the story of a woman living in Bhaktapur (Nepal).
She lost her house with everything inside during the awful earthquake of 2015 that hit very hard the Kathmandu Valley.
She is still living today in a temporary sheet metal shack, that is too warm in summer and too hot in winter.
I met this woman for the first time in a temple close to Durbar square where I "stole" her portrait.
One year later I came back to Bhaktapur and by showing the photo, I looked for the help of local people to find her again.
It was my lucky day, as among the people involved in her research, I met the woman's son who brought me to the sheet metal shack where his mother lives.
The smile of the woman at the sight of her returned portrait paid off all the efforts for finding her.

Edition of 1
